comments.body:
@yannicvandekuit Does the `D:\experiments\Test.ps1` only contain `Write-Output "Test"` in it? If not, can you share the whole `Test.ps1` script?
Can you try `"c:\Program Files\PowerShell\7\pwsh.exe" -noprofile D:\experiments\Test.ps1` and see if you would run into the same problem?
Also, is the `cmd.exe` in the screenshot running as a 32-bit process or 64-bit process? (you can check this in Task Manager, click `Details`, find the process, then check the `Platform` column)
